,Recommended,221180,14996394,"Posted: 21 March, 2015",all,jjm319,"This is an enjoyable game.  I would like to mention the cool sci-fi ideas behind this.  THis game is based on an actual proposed technology called dyson trees. THese would be some sort of replicating technology that could colonize asteroids and bud seeds that could go on to colonize others.  It also is related to a type of space probe called a self replicating Von Neumann machine. So you play as sort of an nanotechnology intelligence embodied in these trees/seed. Pretty cool.The game itself is enjoyable, you can play it at a slow speed for a meditative growing game or crank it up to fast making it a little frenetic. I played the original a while ago. Im not sure what all has been upgraded, but it has better graphics, i think more missions and modes, some extra controls. Get this game."
,Recommended,221180,13192131,"Posted: 1 December, 2014",all,Tipster,"EufloriaFieldRatingReviewGraphics9Eufloria gets a solid nod for the artistic approach it took to graphics. This game weaves together a beautiful living picture as you play, with pleasant and relaxing aesthetics, from sound to visuals.Gameplay7A wonderfully relaxing game, Eufloria is great to sit down and play when you're looking to just chill out. Mesmerizing in style, with a downtone soundtrack, Eufloria offers up a unique take on strategy games. Taking a much more tug of war approach, you grow your seeds (altering their stats via another artful gameplay mechanic) and work to overwhelm the opposing forces. Eventually it becomes a domino effect as you send wave after gigantic wave of units from planet to planet, toppling over the enemy's forces. However, it can be a bit tedious at times waiting for your army to grow enough to make your next move, particularly at the start of each game. This problem is few and far between though, as several times you are under immediate pressure to act.Story3You probably won't find yourself caring much about the story of this game, as it is strange and vague most the time.MultiplayerN/ANone to be found here.Replayability5Eufloria is one of those games you come to when you need it. For me, that particular time is when I need to wind down and relax. Each time coming back is enjoyable though.Overall6/10Don't get confused by the 6 over there, that's still a good number. I definitely recommend Eufloria to anyone that enjoys sitting down and playing a chill game. If you're looking for fast paced action this game is not for you. Eufloria is a moment of calm in a storm of run-and-gun, spray-and-pray, leap-then-look games.If you liked this review, feel free to check out my curator page:The TipsterYou are also welcome to join our group and play/discuss games together, here:The Tipster"
,Recommended,221180,16894911,"Posted: 5 July, 2015",all,Nugget,"Eufloria HD is an upgraded version of the original Eufloria, which I also played.Both games are an extremely relaxing and atmospheric strategy based on some gameplay mechanics from simpler flash strategy titles: capture planets (here called asteroids), upgrade them (here with beautiful trees that grow over time) and they will generate units (here called seedlings) over time, then use said units to flood other asteroids. Take over the map and you win. Rinse and repeat.Despite the fact that the games tend to reach a certain tipping point where it becomes easy to overwhelm your enemies, Eufloria is a very polished take on this idea, and a lot of fun to boot! The soundtrack is very mellow, and the visuals are clean and beautiful.This version upgrades the visuals and adds some new mechanics, such as the ability to upgrade asteroids which have poor stats by sacrificing seedlings, and rallying points which means less needless clicking and dragging.There is a solid story mode that can take about 10 hours to complete (or more depending on what speed you play at), as well as arcade levels and a New Game + mode. Overall, a decent amount of content for the price.Honestly, I cannot recommend this game enough! It has a great, calming atmopshere, some straightforward but satisfying RTS gameplay and a solid campaign and arcade mode. Definitely worth the price!"
,Recommended,221180,32891014,Posted: 27 June,all,Thaiauxn,"Eufloria is fantastic. Smart, simple, a cool and mysterious story with inspiring sci-fi elements presented in a mythical manner.There are plenty of indie games that look really cool when you see their art and design that you think will be okay, then fall flat on their face with disappointing gameplay. Eufloria does not do that. It is amazingly fun and intuitive after a few minutes, with interesting challenges as you continue that make following the text based mystery even more exciting. It does get challenging, but if you need help, this is one of the only games with in-game hints that are actually super helpful. No random variables thrown in to frustrate you - if you mess up you know it's because you haven't figured out this tactic yet, not because the challenge is arbitrary.I did not know it was a hybrid RTS-Tactical Problem Solver. I just thought it looked pretty. I was very happily surprised that the game was basically exactly what I wanted.Absolutely worth the full price.I got it on the summer steam sale for 3$ - I also got a bunch of others, and so far Eufloria is not only the best of them, but is carrying the banner for how good and indie game can be. And should be."
