,Recommended,221180,13080715,"Posted: 25 November, 2014",all,RPINerd,"Eufloria (and it’s HD upgrade) are strategy games at the core, however I’m not sure what sub genre they fall into. Similar to games like Galcon, the goal is to plant your seed on large planets, allow forces to build up, then swarm the next planet to expand. It feels a lot like the combat within an RTS, but simplified down immensely and without any base building aspects.That being said, it’s not a bad game. I first played it on mobile and I think the simplicity of the format works well with a touch screen,  however when making the switch to PC I found that I felt very idle in the game. With a mouse, keyboard and macros I have infinitely more micromanaging power than when I’m toilet gaming with two thumbs. Because of this, I find that this isn’t a very compelling title to own on PC. Eufloria (and Eufloria HD) are good games and I do recommend you give them a go, but be fully aware that you’re going into a more mobile-minded experience."
