,Recommended,221180,25328286,"Posted: 3 September, 2016",all,kazerniel,"A fun and minimalistic real-time strategy. I mostly played with the Classic version, which isn't displayed on the recorded hours above.Classic - Recommended!+ very intuitive controls+ simple and good visuals (turn on faction icons in the options!)+ good ambient sounds+ an option to choose between faster and slower gameplay- very long turns without a save option - you have to invest at least an hour or so in one sitting, as there's no save option while playing a map (because of this I wouldn't call this a casual game)- extremely lacking tutorial: barely anything is explained, I had to figure out multiple essential things in the hard way and with fan guides (40 unit limit for seedling production, what the flower and the mine do, and which is which visually)- very micromanagement-heavy and kinda monotonous gameplay- glitchy graphics in full screen mode, so I have to keep it in windowed, which has a fixed (small) window sizeHD - kinda meh, play Classic instead+ a lot more comprehensive tutorial- the graphics are marginally prettier, but when the player zooms out the seedlings don't turn into dots of light like in the Classic version, but shrink into near-invisibility, making the graphics actually way less usable than in the original- more precise, but a lot less intuitive controls - sending seedlings (the most common task) requires more time and clicks than in the Classic versionVerdictI really recommend the Classic version (just check out the options, and read some online guides if you get stuck).Regardless of the better tutorial, the two negatives I listed at the HD version made the gameplay so much more frustrating that I quickly gave up on that version."
