,Recommended,221180,17936205,"Posted: 7 September, 2015",all,Mazian,"A 3X strategy game sporting a minimalistic art direction is given fresh life in Eufloria HD. Eschewing complex space combat, which is the dominating genre for the 4X game, in Eufloria you take on the guise of a organic army that has set out to plant itself around the game space. Eufloria sports a couple of ""super units"" each with their own special abilities, two types of ""base structures"" and a simple upgrade system which adds depth to an deceptively complex strategy game. Not many hours of first-play-through time, but at its standard low price its quite enjoyable. Once you have defeated the campaign it garners replayability through ""arena"" modes and a second play through of the campaign at higher difficulty, entitled ""Dark Mode."" I recommend this."
,Recommended,221180,17476325,"Posted: 10 August, 2015",all,Pumpkin,"Eufloria is a game where you colonise asteroids and engage in seed warfare against ""the greys"". The concept is really simple: Plant trees to create seeds and defend your asteroids, send seeds out to colonise other asteroids and potentially take them by force. then continue to grow your colony.In description and presentation Eufloria appears basic and casual which you wouldn't be wrong if you said it was however as you play new elements are introduced to add extra layers of strategy. Eufloria is relaxing and simple but that's only because it takes you through the mechanics of the game at such a pase that you easily learn and form new strategies. Additionally the game has 3 speed settings so wether you'd like a casual relaxing experience or a fast paced strategy setting it's your decision.Eufloria is a fun game for those looking for a different experience or maybe if you just want to relax. For the price and the ammount of content it's money well spent."
