,Recommended,221180,13629242,"Posted: 26 December, 2014",all,Merinator,"Long story short: I love itI've clocked in... too many hours playing this game in it's original form. I enjoy this sort of game though I'm sure it's not for everyone - try the demo first if you're concerned. The updated HD version is a little bit different in the mechanics but I've already gotten used to it and I think it's for the best.My work requires that I be rather creative and that can be a big mental drain sometimes. This game has been a great way for me to wind down after a long day. There's still plenty of thinking involved but the ambient sounds/music makes a relaxing atmostphere even when my minions are getting slaughtered. I also appreciate the fact that the game doesn't really force me to be something I'm not - there are some levels where speed or sneakiness wins the day but typically, you play the strategy you like best and as long as you play well, you'll win.The storyline is fairly simple, just enough to carry you from mission to mission, teaching you different strategies. I kind of wish more games taught this way in their campaign modes. Maybe to some it seems like hand-holding, though. Regardless, I appreciate not having to think so hard in a game while still feeling engaged.The downsides: not much. It is what it is - an 'ambient strategy game'. Sometimes the really big missions get a bit boring when you have to wait for enough seedlings to accumulate in order to make a key move. The new speed change option in the HD version pretty much fixes that issue for me, however. But still no co-op. I think they're could be great potential there... maybe in Eufloria 2 or something?"
