76561198041399191,Recommended,221180,20623756,"Posted: 19 January, 2016",all,I Kinda Fail,"I really liked the original Eufloria for its simplistic, yet strategic, gameplay. The music is relaxing and the graphics, while nothing special to look at, light up the dark landscapes beautifully. There's two ways to play - from a distant standpoint, watching the battlefield as blips on a radar, or up close and personal, where those little dots turn into your fleet, blasting the enemy and invading their planets.The original did feel more balanced, as I feel like a few of the HD levels weren't intended for some of the new features. For example, one of the maps, Hide and Seek, intended for you to abandon your previous planets and move onto the enemy's stronger planets. In HD, they added a feature to strengthen your planets by sacrificing soldiers, so you can simply farm seedlings on a throwaway planet and bolster a crappy planet's stats until it can take on a giant, taking away from the level's original goals.The fast forward feature is a blessing in HD, and it'll be hard to go back to the original for this reason alone. The only thing it's missing is a multiplayer feature!"
